{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"3253866e-603a-41cc-9faa-460ecee05f77","content":"## What happened\n\nApple removed DSA from its native cryptographic libraries (Security.framework). The .NET runtime on macOS delegates to platform crypto, so once Apple dropped DSA, `DSA.Create()` throws **`PlatformNotSupportedException`** on macOS. This is a documented breaking change — it worked in earlier .NET versions only because the Apple API hadn't been removed yet.\n\n## How to fix it\n\nYou have three options, in order of effort:\n\n### 1. Use `DSAOpenSsl` explicitly (smallest change)\nInstall OpenSSL on macOS (e.g. `brew install openssl`) and target it directly:\n\n```csharp\nusing System.Security.Cryptography;\n\n// Instead of DSA.Create(), use the OpenSSL-backed implementation\nusing var dsa = new DSAOpenSsl();\ndsa.ImportSubjectPublicKeyInfo(publicKeyBytes, out _);\nbool valid = dsa.VerifyData(data, signature, HashAlgorithmName.SHA1);\n```\n\nThis works on Linux (already uses OpenSSL) and macOS (with Homebrew OpenSSL). On Windows the platform-native DSA still works, so you can branch:\n\n```csharp\nDSA CreateDsa() => OperatingSystem.IsWindows()\n    ? DSA.Create()\n    : new DSAOpenSsl();\n```\n\n### 2. Use BouncyCastle (no native dependency)\n\n```bash\ndotnet add package BouncyCastle.Cryptography\n```\n\n```csharp\nusing Org.BouncyCastle.Crypto.Parameters;\nusing Org.BouncyCastle.Security;\n\nvar verifier = SignerUtilities.GetSigner(\"SHA1withDSA\");\nverifier.Init(forSigning: false, publicKeyParam);\nverifier.BlockUpdate(data, 0, data.Length);\nbool valid = verifier.VerifySignature(signature);\n```\n\nPure managed code — no platform crypto dependency at all.\n\n### 3. Migrate away from DSA (best long-term)\n\nDSA is a legacy algorithm. If you control both signing and verification, re-sign with **ECDSA** or **Ed25519**, which are supported everywhere.\n\n---\n\n**Recommendation:** If you only need to *verify* existing legacy signatures and can't re-sign, option 2 (BouncyCastle) is the most portable — no OpenSSL install required on CI/CD or end-user machines.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"807d79a0-bcaf-449a-aad3-70dfe3064feb","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user is asking about a .NET compatibility issue with DSA (Digital Signature Algorithm) on macOS after upgrading from .NET 10 to .NET 11. Let me think about what I know about this topic.\n\nThis is a known breaking change in .NET. Starting with .NET 7+, Microsoft has been deprecating and removing older cryptographic algorithms. Specifically, DSA on macOS has been a known issue because Apple's Security framework (and CommonCrypto/CryptoKit) dropped support for DSA.\n\nLet me recall the specifics:\n\nIn .NET 7, `DSA.Create()` on macOS started throwing `PlatformNotSupportedException` because Apple removed DSA support from their cryptographic libraries. The .NET runtime on macOS relied on Apple's native crypto libraries, and since Apple dropped DSA support, .NET couldn't provide it either.\n\n\nI need to be careful about the timeline here. The user is asking specifically about .NET 10 to .NET 11, and I should focus on what I know with certainty rather than speculating about version-specific details I'm not sure about. documented breaking change that happened in .NET 7 when Apple removed DSA support from macOS's security frameworks. Since .NET relies on the native platform crypto libraries, `DSA.Create()` now throws `PlatformNotSupportedException` on macOS. The main workaround is to use OpenSSL instead of the platform's crypto implementation, either through the `System.Security.Cryptography.OpenSsl` package or by configuring .NET to use OpenSSL on macOS. With BouncyCastle, I get a pure managed implementation that works cross-platform without needing OpenSSL installed. The best path forward though is migrating to a modern algorithm like ECDSA or RSA, which would require re-signing but solves the problem long-term.","outputTokens":1655,"requestId":"3011:56792:179FCFB:1A5CE25:6A067BAC"},"id":"82aad97c-a381-4917-82b2-e85ce492169b","timestamp":"2026-05-15T01:50:06.283Z","parentId":"9510f3e7-4e72-4b52-b6ae-19a9a0a32713"}
